<subSubSection pageId="30" pageNumber="31" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="30.[151,1437,151,1463]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,335,1152,1177]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Comments.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[344,588,1152,1176]" class="Insecta" family="Leucospidae" genus="Leucospis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="opalescens">
<emphasis box="[344,588,1152,1176]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Leucospis opalescens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is an endemic Brazilian species, which was previously recorded from the Amazon and Pantanal. The new records presented here extends its distribution southwestward to the Brazilian Savannah (
<figureCitation box="[274,361,1223,1248]" captionStart="FIGURE 25" captionStartId="40.[151,250,1890,1912]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,526,1869]" captionTargetId="figure@40.[151,1436,526,1869]" captionTargetPageId="40" captionText="FIGURE 25. Geographic records of Leucospis in Brazil, based on literature." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1298019/files/figure.png" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Figs 25</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[373,405,1223,1248]" captionStart="FIGURE 26" captionStartId="41.[151,250,1665,1687]" captionTargetBox="[177,1411,195,1636]" captionTargetId="figure@41.[177,1411,195,1636]" captionTargetPageId="41" captionText="FIGURE 26. New geographic records of Leucospis in Brazil A. Detail of the state of Minas Gerais. B. New records in Brazil." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1298021/files/figure.png" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">26</figureCitation>
